# Security Rules

- Treat all user input, external API responses, files, env vars, URLs, and database values as untrusted.
- Validate input at trust boundaries.
- Do not hardcode secrets, tokens, credentials, private keys, or production URLs.
- Do not log secrets, PII, auth headers, cookies, session IDs, or payment data.
- Use parameterized queries or ORM-safe APIs. Never concatenate SQL.
- Keep authorization checks server-side.
- Fail closed for auth, permissions, payments, and data access.
- For destructive actions, require explicit confirmation in code paths where appropriate.
- Prefer allowlists over blocklists.